          <h2 class="mt-5">What a mortgage underwriter does &mdash; and how to become one</h2>
          <p class="lede">A mortgage underwriter evaluates the completed loan file against guidelines and decides whether to approve it. It rewards analytical, risk-minded people who apply detailed rules consistently.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="body-text">
          <p>If you're researching how to become a mortgage underwriter, know that it's an analytical, guideline-driven role that usually doesn't require an originator license but does demand deep loan knowledge.</p>
          <p>Underwriting is typically salaried. The uncapped income in mortgages belongs to licensed originators, so if a higher ceiling appeals to you, see <a class="inline-link" href="/mortgage-career/loan-officer/">how to become a loan officer</a>.</p>
